Which of the following is NOT a recommended practice to reduce the risk of infection during pregnancy?

a) Wash hands before eating, after touching the ground or petting an animal; wash fruit and vegetables;
b) Cook meat; be careful with cat litter;
c) Avoid eating away from home.
d) Use gloves when cleaning the cat's litter tray and doing the gardening.

Which of the following is NOT a manifestation of suicidal crisis?

a) Non-specific symptoms from the depressive or anxious register; consumption of psychoactive substances (alcohol, illicit substances, tobacco); reckless risk-taking;
b) Withdrawal from affection and physical contact;
c) Isolation.

option_b:
Non-specific symptoms from the depressive or anxious register; consumption of psychoactive substances (alcohol, illicit substances, tobacco);
b) Reckless risk-taking;
c) Isolation.

option_c:
Reduced sense of values;

a) Non-specific symptoms from the depressive or anxious register; consumption of psychoactive substances (alcohol, illicit substances, tobacco); reckless risk-taking;
b) Withdrawal from affection and physical contact;
c) Isolation.
